  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The formalism of next-to-leading order (NLO) Fermi Liquid Theory (FLT) is employed to calculate the thermal properties of symmetric nuclear and pure neutron matter in a relativistic many-body theory beyond the mean field level which includes two-loop (TL) effects. For all thermal variables, the semi-analytical NLO corrections reproduce results of the exact numerical calculations for entropies per baryon up to 2. This corresponds to excellent agreement down to subnuclear densities for temperatures up to 20 MeV. In addition to providing physical insights, a rapid evaluation of the equation of state (EOS) in the homogeneous phase of hot and dense matter is achieved through the use of the zero-temperature Landau effective mass function and its derivatives.</subfield>
